I've now examined all the critical files. I have a complete picture of the architecture. Now I'll produce the comprehensive ULTRAPLAN.

---

# 🔥 ULTRAPLAN: Complete Visual Redesign — AlphaClaw Apex Style

## Executive Summary

Redesign 25 web pages across 3 applications (MAGI v2, Council Room Legacy, Paul Simulator) to the AlphaClaw Apex design language. The cornerstone change: replace Inter with JetBrains Mono everywhere, replace indigo (#818cf8) with cyan (#63ebff), replace gradient orbs with grid texture, add page transition animations, and implement staggered entry + count-up micro-animations.

**Current state:** 18 MAGI pages share `core.css` + `components.css` + `nav.js`. Council Room legacy (3 pages) has independent inline CSS. D&D app (3 pages) has its own `styles.css` + `guide.html` inline CSS + `flow.html` inline CSS.

**Estimated total lines to modify:** ~12,000 lines across 25 files + 4 shared files.

---

## 1. SHARED DESIGN SYSTEM — New `core.css`

Replace `~/magi-v2/frontend/shared/core.css` entirely with:

```css
